programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.sub-title: Last-Minute Winner (Something to Write Home About)
programme.desc: Irita Marriott and Ishy Khan search for antiques and artefacts in Hingham, Norfolk, the ancestral home of the 16th president of the USA, Abraham Lincoln. Ishy blows his cash on Chinese bellows, a vintage glass salt dish and an early 20th-century inkwell. programme.title: Make It at Market

programme.title: The Finish Line

The winner then races against the track itself in an attempt to win the cash prize.(n)

programme.title: Pointless

programme.desc: Arriving on Merseyside in 2004 as part of a freshly recruited Spanish contingent to help build a new-look Liverpool side, Luis Garcia soon became a cult hero at Anfield. But it wasn’t always plain sailing for the Catalonian. In this week’s Big Interview, Garcia shares the difficulties he faced adjusting to the Premier League, how Rafa Benitez managed to hone his talents and his thoughts on that famous “ghost” goal against Chelsea in the 2005 Champions League semi-final.(n)
